   "source": [
    "# Toolkit Example 2: Insert Nodes and Pipes via SirGraf Python Console"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This Example demonstrates how to generate Toolkit commands that create a graph of nodes and pipes in a SIR 3S model. The user is encouraged to copy the code into the sript tab of the SIR 3S Python console to create the graph in a model. It is also demonstrated how to use Toolkit to get model data of node and pipes and create a networkx graph based on it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Generate Toolkit Commands from NX Graph"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def generate_toolkit_commands(graph, session_name=\"DefaultSession\"):\n",
    "    commands = [\n",
    "        \"import PythonWrapperToolkit\",\n",
    "        \"import Sir3S_Repository.Interfaces as Interfaces\",\n",
    "        \"s3s = PythonWrapperToolkit.SIR3S_Model()\",\n",
    "        f\"s3s.StartTransaction(SessionName='{session_name}')\"\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Generate commands for nodes\n",
    "    for node in graph.nodes(data=True):\n",
    "        node_tk = node[0]\n",
    "        x_coord = node[1]['x']\n",
    "        y_coord = node[1]['y']\n",
    "        z_coord = node[1]['z']\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Create the command to insert the node\n",
    "        insert_command = f\"node{node_tk} = s3s.InsertElement(ElementType=Interfaces.Sir3SObjectTypes.Node)\"\n",
    "        commands.append(insert_command)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Create the commands to set the node's coordinates\n",
    "        set_x_command = f\"s3s.SetValue(node{node_tk}, 'Xkor', '{x_coord}')\"\n",
    "        set_y_command = f\"s3s.SetValue(node{node_tk}, 'Ykor', '{y_coord}')\"\n",
    "        set_z_command = f\"s3s.SetValue(node{node_tk}, 'Zkor', '{z_coord}')\"\n",
    "        commands.append(set_x_command)\n",
    "        commands.append(set_y_command)\n",
    "        commands.append(set_z_command)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Generate commands for pipes\n",
    "    for edge in graph.edges(data=True):\n",
    "        node1, node2 = edge[0], edge[1]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Create the command to insert the pipe\n",
    "        pipe_tk = f\"pipe{node1}_{node2}\"\n",
    "        insert_pipe_command = f\"{pipe_tk} = s3s.InsertElement(ElementType=Interfaces.Sir3SObjectTypes.Pipe)\"\n",
    "        commands.append(insert_pipe_command)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Create the command to connect the pipe with nodes\n",
    "        connect_command = f\"s3s.ConnectConnectingElementWithNodes({pipe_tk}, node{node1}, node{node2})\"\n",
    "        commands.append(connect_command)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # End the transaction\n",
    "    commands.append(\"s3s.EndTransaction()\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return commands"
   ]
  },

      "s3s.ConnectConnectingElementWithNodes(pipe5_6, node5, node6)\n",
      "s3s.EndTransaction()\n"
     ]

    "# Function to create a random graph on a 2500x2500 grid\n",
    "def create_random_graph(num_nodes, num_edges):\n",
    "    G = nx.Graph()\n",
    "    for i in range(1, num_nodes + 1):\n",
    "        x = random.randint(0, 2500)\n",
    "        y = random.randint(0, 2500)\n",
    "        G.add_node(i, x=x, y=y, z=0)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for _ in range(num_edges):\n",
    "        node1 = random.randint(1, num_nodes)\n",
    "        node2 = random.randint(1, num_nodes)\n",
    "        if node1 != node2:\n",
    "            G.add_edge(node1, node2)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return G"
   ]

   "source": [
    "# Create NetworkX graph from SIR 3S Model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## s3s"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Initialization complete\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "s3s = PythonWrapperToolkit.SIR3S_Model()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# file path\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    from PT3S import dxAndMxHelperFcts\n",
    "except:\n",
    "    import dxAndMxHelperFcts\n",
    "dbFilename=\"Toolkit_Example1\"\n",
    "dbFile=os.path.join(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(dxAndMxHelperFcts.__file__))\n",
    "                    +'/Examples/Toolkit_Examples/'\n",
    "                    +dbFilename\n",
    "                    +'.db3'\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Model is open for further operation\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "s3s.OpenModel(dbName=dbFile, \n",
    "                   providerType=Interfaces.SirDBProviderType.SQLite, \n",
    "                   Mid=\"M-1-0-1\",\n",
    "                   saveCurrentlyOpenModel = True,\n",
    "                   namedInstance=\"\", \n",
    "                   userID=\"\",\n",
    "                   password=\"\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 31,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "node_tks = s3s.GetTksofElementType(ElementType=Interfaces.Sir3SObjectTypes.Node)\n",
    "pipe_tks = s3s.GetTksofElementType(ElementType=Interfaces.Sir3SObjectTypes.Pipe)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "nodes_data = []\n",
    "pipes_data = []"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Retrieve node data\n",
    "for node_tk in node_tks:\n",
    "    x_coord, _ = s3s.GetValue(node_tk, 'Xkor')\n",
    "    y_coord, _ = s3s.GetValue(node_tk, 'Ykor')\n",
    "    node_name, _ = s3s.GetValue(node_tk, 'Name')\n",
    "    nodes_data.append({\n",
    "        'node_tk': node_tk,\n",
    "        'node_name': node_name,\n",
    "        'x_coord': x_coord.replace(',', '.'),\n",
    "        'y_coord': y_coord.replace(',', '.')\n",
    "    })"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 34,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Retrieve pipe data\n",
    "for pipe_tk in pipe_tks:\n",
    "    from_node, _ = s3s.GetValue(pipe_tk, 'FromNode.Name')\n",
    "    to_node, _ = s3s.GetValue(pipe_tk, 'ToNode.Name')\n",
    "    pipes_data.append({\n",
    "        'pipe_tk': pipe_tk,\n",
    "        'from_node': from_node,\n",
    "        'to_node': to_node\n",
    "    })"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 35,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "nodes_df = pd.DataFrame(nodes_data)\n",
    "pipes_df = pd.DataFrame(pipes_data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 36,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Filter out nodes with x < 700000 and y < 5000000\n",
    "nodes_df['x_coord'] = nodes_df['x_coord'].astype(float)\n",
    "nodes_df['y_coord'] = nodes_df['y_coord'].astype(float)\n",
    "filtered_nodes_df = nodes_df[(nodes_df['x_coord'] >= 700000) & (nodes_df['y_coord'] >= 5000000)]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 37,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "G = nx.Graph()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 38,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Add nodes\n",
    "for _, row in filtered_nodes_df.iterrows():\n",
    "    G.add_node(row['node_tk'], x=row['x_coord'], y=row['y_coord'], z=0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 39,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Add edges (pipes) between nodes\n",
    "for _, row in pipes_df.iterrows():\n",
    "    from_node_name = row['from_node']\n",
    "    to_node_name = row['to_node']\n",
    "    from_node_tk = filtered_nodes_df[filtered_nodes_df['node_name'] == from_node_name]['node_tk'].values[0]\n",
    "    to_node_tk = filtered_nodes_df[filtered_nodes_df['node_name'] == to_node_name]['node_tk'].values[0]\n",
    "    if from_node_tk in G.nodes and to_node_tk in G.nodes:\n",
    "        G.add_edge(from_node_tk, to_node_tk)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   ],
   "source": [
    "pos = {node: (data['x'], data['y']) for node, data in G.nodes(data=True) if 'x' in data and 'y' in data}\n",
    "nx.draw(G, pos, with_labels=False, node_size=10, node_color='skyblue', font_size=10, font_weight='bold')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
